    <div class="text-3xl py-3 font-bold">Student @ Columbia University</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <text class="text-lg">
        I am a quantitative graduate student at Columbia University pursuing an M.A. in Quantitative Methods in the Social Sciences, with a strong foundation in economics, and computer science from Boston University. I focus on applying data-driven analysis to understand market trends and investment opportunities.
        
        I thrive at the intersection of data and decision-making, with experience in investment banking and fixed income research through internships at CICC and Haitong Securities. My work has included IPO valuation, financial due diligence, and bond risk assessment using Bloomberg, Wind, and Capital IQ.
        
        With strong training in machine learning and econometrics, I bring a quantitative mindset to financial analysis. Currently seeking 2026 internship opportunities in financial analytics.
